'''
Polymorphism : It is one of the core concepts in object-oriented programming. The word 'Polymorphism' is derived from Greek language which means "Many Forms". 
It is the ability of an object to take many forms. It allows to perform different actions in different contexts even if the names of the methods are the same.
'''

class cat:
    def sound(self):
        print('Cat Meows!')

class dog:
    def sound(self):
        print('Dog barks!')

class test:
    def sound_check(self, animal):
        animal.sound()

d = dog()
c = cat()


t = test()
t.sound_check(d)

#--------------------------------------

Output:
Dog barks!








